cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NA 

The paper proposes a fast algorithm for high-dimensional bilateral and nonlocal means filtering, which is a common image processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The algorithm involves clustering and fast convolutions, which are common techniques in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian approximations, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
